    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In Christi nomine. Die veneris qui fuit quarto die intrante mense aprilis.
                        Qualiter <rs key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonorum virorum</rs> presentia
                        nomina quorum hic inferius leguntur. De lite et altercatione quam movebat et
                        faciebat <persName key="#childOf #Judicial_breve #Landed_possessions"><name
                                ref="Mantuanus">Mantuanus</name></persName>, <rs key="#childOf"
                            >filius</rs>
                        <persName key="#parentOf"><name ref="Iohannes/grammaticus"
                            >Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs>gramatici</rs>, de <rs key="#Landed_possessions">duobus iugeribus
                            terrę</rs> quę fuere patrui sui, <persName><name ref="Guicomannus"
                                >Guicomanno</name></persName>, qui ex parte <orgName
                            key="#Judicial_breve #Landed_possessions #Churches #Abbots"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti</orgName> possidebat. Sic
                        diffinita est, sub iudicio <rs key="#Count #Judicial_breve">comitis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count">Abbatis</persName>, cui querimonia facta fuit.
                        Quoniam comes, consilio <rs key="#Judge">iudicum</rs>, silicet <persName
                            key="#Judge #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Aribrandus/iudex"
                                >Ariprandi</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge #Judicial_breve"
                                ><name ref="Petrusbonus/iudex">Petriboni</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Rodufus/iudex"
                                >Rodulfi</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge #Judicial_breve"
                                ><name ref="Lanfrancus/iudex">Lanfranci</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Mutellus/iudex"
                            >Mutelli</name></persName>, legitimos <rs key="#Witness">testes</rs>
                        recepit, qui iureiurando firmaverunt esse iuris Sancti Benedicti per datum
                        Martini gramatici predictam terram unde lis erat; et sic ratione cognita,
                        Petrusbonus iudex, iussione comitis Abbatis et consiolio eius ac iudicum,
                        absolvit <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> Sancti Benedicti et ipsum
                        Guicomannum a petitione predicti Mantuani de predicta terra. Et hoc factum
                        fuit in presentia domini <persName key="#Bishops #Witness #Judicial_breve"
                            >Grasindonii</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Archpriests #Witness #Judicial_breve"><name
                                ref="Rigitius/archipresbiter">Rigizonis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archpriests">archipresbiteri</rs> […] et domni <persName
                            key="#Abbots #Witness #Judicial_breve">Uberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs> Sancti Benedicti et domni <persName
                            key="#Priors #Witness #Judicial_breve">Adę</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priors">prioris</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/2416">Sancti Martini</orgName> et domni
                            <persName key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Bonus"
                            >Boni</name></persName>. Actum est hoc in claustro <orgName
                            key="#Priors" ref="#juridical_persons/1426">Sancti Petri</orgName>. In
                        millesimo centesimo quinquagesimo secundo, indictione XV. Haec sunt nomina
                        illorum qui iuraverunt: <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness #Judicial_breve"><name
                                ref="Milo/de Orlando">Milo</name></persName> de <persName><name
                                ref="Rodelandus">Or[la]ndo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness #Judicial_breve"><name
                                ref="Ambrosius/Fricavena">Ambrosius Fricavena</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness #Judicial_breve"><name
                                ref="Tedaldus/de Verderi">Tedaldus</name></persName> de
                            <placeName>Verderi</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus #Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness #Judicial_breve"
                                ><name ref="Lanfrancus/castaldus">Lanfrancus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">castaldus</rs> Milonis de Orlando et
                            <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus #Boni_viri/boni_homines #Witness #Judicial_breve #parentOf"
                                ><name ref="Martinus/castaldus">Martinus</name></persName>
                        castaldus. Isti vero homines ibi interfuerunt: <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Sigefredus/de Sancta Agata"
                                >Siginfredus</name></persName> de <placeName>Sancta
                            Agathe</placeName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name
                                ref="Wido/de Turre">Guido</name></persName> de Turre, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Oddo/de Geza"
                            >Oddo</name></persName> de Geza, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Albertus/Azonis/Enrici"
                                >Albertus</name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Azo/Enrici">Azonis</name></persName>
                        <persName><name ref="Heinricus">Enrici</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judicial_breve"><name ref="Peregrinus/beccarius"
                                >Pelegrinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Specialized_workers">beccarius</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judicial_breve #childOf"><name ref="Gandulfus"
                                >Gandulfinus</name></persName> filius Martini castaldi, qui rogati
                        sunt [te]stes. (SN) Ego <persName key="#Notary #Writer #Judicial_breve"
                            ref="#people/3720">Albertus Castellanus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palatii his interfui et hoc <rs
                            key="#Judicial_breve">breve</rs> iussione comitis <rs key="#Writer"
                            >scripsi</rs>. </ab>
